"mainPid":327782,"title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> Scaling QPixmap","slug":"67138/scaling-qpixmap","timestamp":1463476268428,"lastposttime":1463476401204,"postcount":3,"viewcount":15,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327784","relativeTime":"2016-05-17T09:11:08.428Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-17T09:13:21.204Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"AlvaroS","userslug":"alvaros","email":"alvaro.salcedo90@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/23f3137333db44ea8018b873681dde3b?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"","signature":"","reputation":13,"postcount":56,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":28139,"icon:text":"A","icon:bgColor":"#e65100"},"teaser":{"pid":327784,"uid":25369,"tid":67138,"content":"<p><a class=\"plugin-mentions-a\" href=\"https://forum.qt.io/user/alvaros\">@AlvaroS</a><br />\nHello,<br />\nYoure not actually changing the pixmap. Look at the documentation of <a href=\"http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qpixmap.html#scaledToHeight\" rel=\"nofollow\">QPixmap::scaledToHeight</a>. Try something like this:</p>\nimg_scene = img_scene.scaledToHeight(my_height);\nimg_scene = img_scene.scaledToWidth(my_width);\n\n<p>Kind regards.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-17T09:13:21.204Z","user":{"username":"kshegunov","userslug":"kshegunov","email":"kshegunov@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9296f2b3c8c9866793455bf2c26a6195?size=192&d=mm","uid":25369,"icon:text":"K","icon:bgColor":"#009688"},"index":3},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67137,"uid":26938,"cid":10,"mainPid":"327780","title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> How to open a temporary file use QDesktopServices?","slug":"67137/how-to-open-a-temporary-file-use-qdesktopservices","timestamp":1463475718590,"lastposttime":1463475876137,"postcount":2,"viewcount":7,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327781","relativeTime":"2016-05-17T09:01:58.590Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-17T09:04:36.137Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"ljc123456gogo","userslug":"ljc123456gogo","email":"501297819@qq.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/40eeeb99c3b94e7c268033c5cb5ac9b1?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"LJCDUO","signature":"Keep Hungery, Keep Foolish!","reputation":1,"postcount":23,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":26938,"icon:text":"L","icon:bgColor":"#f44336"},"teaser":{"pid":327781,"uid":18260,"tid":67137,"content":"<p><a class=\"plugin-mentions-a\" href=\"https://forum.qt.io/user/ljc123456gogo\">@ljc123456gogo</a> said:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>QTemporaryFile</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Hi<br />\nas long as its not a .exe file, you should be able to<br />\nuse QTemporaryFile to get file name. delete the QTemporaryFile object to release file<br />\nand reuse the tempname for a file you then create normally.<br />\nThere is also<br />\n<a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/c/tmpnam\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/c/tmpnam</a></p>\n<p>And dont call filename anything with setup. on windows, its forbidden. :)<br />\nUAC eats it in win 10.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-17T09:04:36.137Z","user":{"username":"mrjj","userslug":"mrjj","email":"jeh@pedax.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bdb648df61ad37e4592e194063f4a784?size=192&d=mm","uid":18260,"icon:text":"M","icon:bgColor":"#e91e63"},"index":2},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67111,"uid":2820,"cid":10,"mainPid":327629,"title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> Set DPI for QPixmap?","slug":"67111/set-dpi-for-qpixmap","timestamp":1463409579006,"lastposttime":1463475445406,"postcount":3,"viewcount":37,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327778","relativeTime":"2016-05-16T14:39:39.006Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-17T08:57:25.406Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"c.savur","userslug":"c-savur","email":"c.savur@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/336866a4867d85b3fd2702da2d0d987c?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"Celal","signature":"","reputation":4,"postcount":18,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":2820,"icon:text":"C","icon:bgColor":"#009688"},"teaser":{"pid":327778,"uid":10616,"tid":67111,"content":"<p>what happens if you do the following?</p>\nQImage img(...);  // your image\nQPixmap pix( image.size() );  // not sure if this size is correct of if it has to be recalculated considering the dpi ratio\nQPainter p(&amp;pix);\np.drawImage( 0, 0, img );\n\n","timestamp":"2016-05-17T08:57:25.406Z","user":{"username":"raven-worx","userslug":"raven-worx","email":"info@raven-worx.net","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a8965944c97d83c0bcbb1e860533148d?size=192&d=mm","uid":10616,"icon:text":"R","icon:bgColor":"#607d8b"},"index":3},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67006,"uid":28932,"cid":13,"mainPid":327153,"title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> [ISSUE] QtCreator 3.6.0, 3.6.1 and 4.0.0 do not start up on windows","slug":"67006/issue-qtcreator-3-6-0-3-6-1-and-4-0-0-do-not-start-up-on-windows","timestamp":1463124583245,"lastposttime":1463474930539,"postcount":6,"viewcount":64,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327777","relativeTime":"2016-05-13T07:29:43.245Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-17T08:48:50.539Z","category":{"cid":13,"name":"To