ead":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67098,"uid":28912,"cid":48,"mainPid":327576,"title":"<span class=\"answered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Solved</span> Comments &#x2F; posts moderation on Qt Blog","slug":"67098/comments-posts-moderation-on-qt-blog","timestamp":1463383986728,"lastposttime":1463470258380,"postcount":5,"viewcount":72,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":1,"teaserPid":"327764","relativeTime":"2016-05-16T07:33:06.728Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-17T07:30:58.380Z","category":{"cid":48,"name":"Qt Contribution","icon":"fa-pencil-square-o","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"48/qt-contribution","disabled":false},"user":{"uid":0,"username":"[[global:guest]]","fullname":null,"userslug":"","reputation":null,"postcount":null,"picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d41d8cd98f00b204e9800998ecf8427e?size=192&d=mm","signature":null,"banned":null,"status":null,"email":null,"icon:text":"?","icon:bgColor":"#aaa"},"teaser":{"pid":327764,"uid":15026,"tid":67098,"content":"<p>The user must have deleted the account.<br />\nIt is a valid user, as they contacted me privately. Im looking into what happened. Initially it seems like the post was stuck in approval, as the blog author hadnt checked the comments in a while. But still working on the details.</p>\n<p>To me it is pretty normal to have users who do not want to share any details anywhere. Apparently this user did not want to leave a nickname here. That happens, and its ok.</p>\n<p>Of course with the forum there is a problem in deleting nicknames, as Qt Account remembers them and when the user wants to rejoin here, they will get the same nickname (not exactly sure what will happen to orphan posts like this if that happens.). So choosing a nickname is important.</p>\n<p>The other take-away here is that people really need to have a channel where they can voice problems when they see them, and someone who takes the issue further. If blog comment approval looks wrong, then it is important to raise it here or in feedback.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-17T07:30:58.380Z","user":{"username":"tekojo","userslug":"tekojo","email":"tero.kojo@qt.io","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/603587eeff8b90a13431e50de263badd?size=192&d=mm","uid":15026,"icon:text":"T","icon:bgColor":"#33691e"},"index":5},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67104,"uid":28951,"cid":12,"mainPid":"327612","title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> Define Enum in coed header and Use it in qml","slug":"67104/define-enum-in-coed-header-and-use-it-in-qml","timestamp":1463400802621,"lastposttime":1463469813595,"postcount":6,"viewcount":57,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327761","relativeTime":"2016-05-16T12:13:22.621Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-17T07:23:33.595Z","category":{"cid":12,"name":"Qt Quick","icon":"fa-paper-plane","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"12/qt-quick","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"Jehyeok","userslug":"jehyeok","email":"jehyeok.lee@3dsystems.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e095b70631382ebb9beb86509cb6030d?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"","signature":"","reputation":0,"postcount":5,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":28951,"icon:text":"J","icon:bgColor":"#2196f3"},"teaser":{"pid":327761,"uid":12047,"tid":67104,"content":"<p><a class=\"plugin-mentions-a\" href=\"https://forum.qt.io/user/jehyeok\">@Jehyeok</a> Are those enums in the class with Q_OBJECT markers ? You can try creating a similar class and then include it in the registered class.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-17T07:23:33.595Z","user":{"username":"p3c0","userslug":"p3c0","email":"dabhadeashish@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8d81205e42ba1fc5b88820b4c9e5df73?size=192&d=mm","uid":12047,"icon:text":"P","icon:bgColor":"#9c27b0"},"index":6},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":