nd now it works.  Ive change the category so I now have a Teensy Microcontrollers under projects (left column), and the display name in the middle, and the description.  I havent changed any of the options, pages, or genertors yet.</p>\n<p>Edit:</p>\n<p>I foundout that if I remove the supported project types line the project will not show up.  I have no idea what this does but its got a list of stuff.</p>\n&quot;supportedProjectTypes&quot;: [ &quot;CMakeProjectManager.CMakeProject&quot;, &quot;Qbs.QbsProject&quot;, &quot;Qt4ProjectManager.Qt4Project&quot; ],\n\n<p>Edit 2:<br />\nThis evidently replaces the kind in the xml wizard.  It has to be there but can be empty as in</p>\n<p>&quot;supportedProjectTypes&quot; : [&quot;&quot;]</p>\n<p>I simply put &quot;project: in and it seemed happy.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-17T02:12:23.063Z","user":{"username":"RangerQT","userslug":"rangerqt","email":"biholcomb@l1049h.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e2b4b6b82cc6630a9f103aed39f6adeb?size=192&d=mm","uid":18513,"icon:text":"R","icon:bgColor":"#9c27b0"},"index":3},"tags":[{"value":"json wizard","color":"","bgColor":"","score":1}],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":66869,"uid":13395,"cid":13,"mainPid":326302,"title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> What JS functions are available in Qt Creator Wizards? Where&#x27;s the documentation?","slug":"66869/what-js-functions-are-available-in-qt-creator-wizards-where-s-the-documentation","timestamp":1462813032682,"lastposttime":1463448942036,"postcount":2,"viewcount":62,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327731","relativeTime":"2016-05-09T16:57:12.682Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-17T01:35:42.036Z","category":{"cid":13,"name":"Tools","icon":"fa-hdd-o","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"13/tools","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"shavera","userslug":"shavera","email":"alexshaver@gmail.com