a href=\"http://lists.qt-project.org/mailman/listinfo/qt-creator\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-16T20:10:59.097Z","user":{"username":"SGaist","userslug":"sgaist","email":"samuel.gaist@edeltech.ch","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/07682a4fa2355ff3ecce1d522458e3e7?size=192&d=mm","uid":5578,"icon:text":"S","icon:bgColor":"#607d8b"},"index":4},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67124,"uid":21140,"cid":10,"mainPid":327687,"title":"<span class=\"answered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Solved</span> Error returning enum type","slug":"67124/error-returning-enum-type","timestamp":1463423833123,"lastposttime":1463424892009,"postcount":7,"viewcount":32,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":1,"teaserPid":"327698","relativeTime":"2016-05-16T18:37:13.123Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-16T18:54:52.009Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"yuvaram","userslug":"yuvaram","email":"yuvaram.aligeti@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5febfb8b66f81718bbda82ffcf232a37?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"Yuvaram Aligeti","signature":"......\nYuvaram\nEmbedded Qt Developer \n.......  : )","reputation":7,"postcount":29,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":21140,"icon:text":"Y","icon:bgColor":"#673ab7"},"teaser":{"pid":327698,"uid":21140,"tid":67124,"content":"<p><a class=\"plugin-mentions-a\" href=\"https://forum.qt.io/user/chris-kawa\">@Chris-Kawa</a><br />\nThank you :)</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-16T18:54:52.009Z","user":{"username":"yuvaram","userslug":"yuvaram","email":"yuvaram.aligeti@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5febfb8b66f81718bbda82ffcf232a37?size=192&d=mm","uid":21140,"icon:text":"Y","icon:bgColor":"#673ab7"},"index":7},"tags":[{"value":"error","color":"","bgColor":"","score":68}],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":66877,"uid":28854,"cid":11,"mainPid":326362,"title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> Embedded Linux &#x2F; Framebuffer &#x2F; No screens available","slug":"66877/embedded-linux-framebuffer-no-screens-available","timestamp":1462841073395,"lastposttime":1463424839637,"postcount":4,"viewcount":56,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327697","relativeTime":"2016-05-10T00:44:33.395Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-16T18:53:59.637Z","category":{"cid":11,"name":"Mobile and Embedded","icon":"fa-mobile","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"11/mobile-and-embedded","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"TopKool","userslug":"topkool","email":"amilcar.batista@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0066f3f309876e9ae468b95ae1bf2c6a?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"","signature":"","reputation":0,"postcount":3,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":28854,"icon:text":"T","icon:bgColor":"#795548"},"teaser":{"pid":327697,"uid":28854,"tid":66877,"content":"<p>I figured out the issue. It was due to our kernel configuration. I still do not know exactly what it is the root cause, but once some custom security features disabled in  the kernel, Qt works.</p>\n<p>Thanks for your support.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-16T18:53:59.637Z","user":{"username":"TopKool","userslug":"topkool","email":"amilcar.batista@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0066f3f309876e9ae468b95ae1bf2c6a?size=192&d=mm","uid":28854,"icon:text":"T","icon:bgColor":"#795548"},"index":4},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67121,"uid":28989,"cid":10,"mainPid":327663,"title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> drag and drop problem","slug":"67121/drag-and-drop-problem","timestamp":1463418313171,"lastposttime":1463424565574,"postcount":2,"viewcount":34,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327693","relativeTime":"2016-05-16T17:05:13.171Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-16T18:49:25.574Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"Zakaria94","userslug":"zakaria94","email":"za.sabti@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6d1b29404c50d9a7742ada6ac69d9c20?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"","signature":"","reputation":0,"postcount":1,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":28989,"icon:text":"Z","icon:bgColor":"#3f51b5"},"teaser":{"pid":327693,"uid":21518,"tid":67121,"content":"<p>Hello and welcome to the community!</p>\n<p>I think that you are making your own life complicated. From what I can see you only want to move a QGraphicsItem around in a QGraphicsScene. You dont want to move them between different widgets - is that correct?<br />\nIf so, I recommend letting QGraphicsScene doing all the hard work: Simply make your item become movable by settings the QGraphicsItem::ItemIsMovable flag to true. From then on you can move your item around by dragging it (click and hold to move and it will stop moving once you release the mouse button). Thats exactly the behavior you want to archive if I interpret your code pieces correctly.<br />\nIf you need your pieces to snap to certain predefined positions you can do that by implementing a Snap-to-Grid behavior in the graphics items itemChange() method.</p>\n<p>To answer your actual question: The warning you mention is what you get when you try to remove an item from a scene that doesnt contain the item. Without further analyzing your code thats most likely the case when you call scene-&gt;removeItem(PionARemplacer); and PionARemplacer isnt assigned to that scene (according to the message you get its not assigned to any scene because it says that the scene is null).<br />\nHowever, what I dont understand is your statement that you cant drop it. The message you get simply tells you that something is wrong with removing the item. However, in your case that shouldnt have any effect at all. Can you further explain the issue that you are facing?</p>\n<p>By the way, a generic remark: Try to avoid using non-english terms in source code. Parceque pas tout le monde parle francais ;)</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-16T18:49:25.574Z","user":{"username":"Joel Bodenmann","userslug":"joel-bodenmann","email":"info@b-electronics.ch","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/64bb5c1dc3c27a3cb45e347326fbdec5?size=192&d=mm","uid":21518,"icon:text":"J","icon:bgColor":"#e65100"},"index":2},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67085,"uid":28967,"cid":10,"mainPid":"327519","title":"<span class=\"answered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Solved</span> This application failed to start because it could not find or load the Qt platform plugin &quot;windows&quot; in &quot;&quot;.","slug":"67085/this-application-failed-to-start-because-it-could-not-find-or-load-the-qt-platform-plugin-windows-in","timestamp":1463336010937,"lastposttime":1463424393390,"postcount":7,"viewcount":88,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":1,"teaserPid":"327690","relativeTime":"2016-05-15T18:13:30.937Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-16T18:46:33.390Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"CeruleanTango","userslug":"ceruleantango","email":"tomdivel@hotmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0c1a220fb230b4b04cd55702bd28fb50?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"","signature":"","reputation":1,"postcount":4,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":28967,"icon:text":"C","icon:bgColor":"#3f51b5"},"teaser":{"pid":327690,"uid":28967,"tid":67085,"content":"<p><a class=\"plugin-mentions-a\" href=\"https://forum.qt.io/user/mrjj\">@mrjj</a> Hi. Thank you for the link.</p>\n<p>However there are several problems Ive found, likely only due to having version 5.6 of Qt. There is no such .exe named HelloQt.exe in the bin folder of the Qt installation.</p>\n<p>Regardless of that fact, adding in the files specified by the link you provided resolved the error, and now running the VS2015 build produces a window as it should. Consider this problem solved.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-16T18:46:33.390Z","user":{"username":"CeruleanTango","userslug":"ceruleantango","email":"tomdivel@hotmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0c1a220fb230b4b04cd55702bd28fb50?size=192&d=mm","uid":28967,"icon:text":"C","icon:bgColor":"#3f51b5"},"index":7},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67044,"uid":28948,"cid":10,"mainPid":"327339","title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> Proper way to manage the ui","slug":"67044/proper-way-to-manage-the-ui","timestamp":1463178318048,"lastposttime":1463423461789,"postcount":5,"viewcount":101,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327685","relativeTime":"2016-05-13T22:25:18.048Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-16T18:31:01.789Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"NicolasKsi","userslug":"nicolasksi","email":"nicolas@casime.com.ar","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fb8b03a0c608d7c7e54fe0727ca7fd8d?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"","signature":"","reputation":0,"postcount":2,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":28948,"icon:text":"N","icon:bgColor":"#f44336"},"teaser":{"pid":327685,"uid":747,"tid":67044,"content":"<p>There are couple of ways to do all this but lets stick to the basics.<br />\nRight click on the project -&gt; Add new -&gt; Qt -&gt; Qt Designer Form Class.<br />\nThis will create a .ui designer file and a .h/.cpp files for a class that uses that ui. If you already have a class and you just want to attach the .ui generated code you can do the above and see how an integration is done.<br />\nOk, lets say you now have a dialog class with a designer ui. Lets call it SomeDialog. As I mentioned earlier its important to pass a parent to a dialog, so that it has proper focus and window ordering, so the basic setup would be:</p>\nvoid MainWindow::someButtonPressed()\n{\n   SomeDialog dialog(this);\n   dialog.exec();\n}\n\n<p>Now to the data passing. There are again couple of ways to do that. One of the easier ones is via a data structure. For a simple example lets say you have a structure that definess some login information:</p>\nstruct LoginData\n{\n    QString login;\n    QString password;\n};\n\n<p>You keep that in your MainWindow:</p>\nclass MainWindow\n{\nprivate:\n   LoginData loginData;\n}\n\n<p>and youd like to fill it in via dialog. You can do that like this for example:</p>\nvoid MainWindow::someButtonPressed()\n{\n   SomeDialog dialog(loginData, this);\n   if (dialog.exec() == QDialog::Accepted)\n       loginData = dialog.data();\n}\n\n<p>For that to work youd have a constructor of your dialog looking something like that:</p>\nSomeDialog::SomeDialog(const LoginData&amp; loginData, QWidget* parent) : QDialog(parent)\n{\n    ui-&gt;loginLineEdit-&gt;setText(loginData.login);\n    ui-&gt;passwordLineEdit-&gt;setText(loginData.password);\n}\n\n<p>and a getter function to retrieve the user input:</p>\nLoginData SomeDialog::data() const\n{\n   LoginData loginData { ui-&gt;loginLineEdit-&gt;text(), ui-&gt;passwordLineEdit-&gt;text() };\n   return loginData;\n}\n\n<p>You can also go with signals/slots. Theres no &quot;one true way&quot;.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-16T18:31:01.789Z","user":{"username":"Chris Kawa","userslug":"chris-kawa","email":"krzysiek.kawa@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/45bb97cd3a32d6468c962c9cd09ae59e?size=192&d=mm","uid":747,"icon:text":"C","icon:bgColor":"#e91e63"},"index":5},"tags":[],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false},{"tid":67079,"uid":28908,"cid":10,"mainPid":"327502","title":"<span class=\"unanswered\"><i class=\"fa fa-question-circle\"></i> Unsolved</span> Linking problem with Vlc Qt library","slug":"67079/linking-problem-with-vlc-qt-library","timestamp":1463320938004,"lastposttime":1463422273035,"postcount":9,"viewcount":107,"locked":false,"deleted":false,"pinned":false,"isQuestion":1,"isSolved":0,"teaserPid":"327684","relativeTime":"2016-05-15T14:02:18.004Z","lastposttimeISO":"2016-05-16T18:11:13.035Z","category":{"cid":10,"name":"General and Desktop","icon":"fa-laptop","bgColor":"#80c342","color":"#FFFFFF","slug":"10/general-and-desktop","disabled":false},"user":{"username":"AyushExel204","userslug":"ayushexel204","email":"thedeveloper.ayush@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/001aab942b3ab21e7c53cda46ea27985?size=192&d=mm","fullname":"","signature":"","reputation":0,"postcount":11,"banned":0,"status":"online","uid":28908,"icon:text":"A","icon:bgColor":"#009688"},"teaser":{"pid":327684,"uid":747,"tid":67079,"content":"<p>Sounds like what I said earlier - the vlc dll was probably compiled with different Qt version than what youre using in your project. These need to match.</p>\n","timestamp":"2016-05-16T18:11:13.035Z","user":{"username":"Chris Kawa","userslug":"chris-kawa","email":"krzysiek.kawa@gmail.com","picture":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/45bb97cd3a32d6468c962c9cd09ae59e?size=192&d=mm","uid":747,"icon:text":"C","icon:bgColor":"#e91e63"},"index":9},"tags":[{"value":"vlc-qt","color":"","bgColor":"","score":4},{"value":"msvc12","color":"","bgColor":"","score":2},{"value":"link error","color":"","bgColor":"","score":2}],"isOwner":false,"unread":true,"unreplied":false}],"nextStart":60,"feeds:disableRSS":false,"rssFeedUrl":"/recent.rss","title":"[[pages:recent]]","breadcrumbs":[{"text":"[[global:home]]","url":"/"},{"text":"[[recent:title]]"}],"loggedIn":false,"relative_path":"","